        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 7:54PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 754 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Ceres, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Wytheville...
Bland...
Marion...
Rural Retreat...
Ceres...
Max Meadows...
and Nebo.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until midnight EDT for
northwestern North Carolina...and southwestern Virginia.</instruction>
